column4: what does it mean when "unzip" says "xxxx.exe may be a plain executable, not an archive"
it doesn't think the .exe file you fed it is a self-extracting archive, it thinks it's just a plain executable file.
hmm, its the driver file for my wi-fi but if i can't extract it, how do i use NDISwrapper?
use wine to run the .exe file and hope it will extract
